Disease Outbreaks Reported
11 February 2000
Viral haemorrhagic fever/Marburg in Democratic Republic of Congo - Update 9
Sporadic suspected cases of Marburg haemorrhagic fever have been reported
from Durba, Democratic Republic of Congo since the last update. A new case
of Marburg has been confirmed by virological tests performed by National
Institute for Virology (NIV), South Africa. The patient was a 30 year-old
gold miner working in a mine in the Durba area, who became ill on 8 January
2000.
Fifteen suspect cases were reported during November and December 1999.
Clinical samples from 12 were submitted to NIV for testing. All of these
were found to be negative for Marburg and
other pathogens.
